{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id567b5c5a-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02","identifier":"/us/usc/t14/s101"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"101"},"text":"§ 101.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Establishment of Coast Guard","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Coast Guard, established ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1915-01-28"},"text":"January 28, 1915","children":[],"tail":", shall be a military service and a branch of the armed forces of the United States at all times."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id567b5c5b-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/496"},"text":"63 Stat. 496","children":[],"tail":", § 1; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/546/s1/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–546, § 1(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2519"},"text":"90 Stat. 2519","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/296/tXVII/s1704/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–296, title XVII, § 1704(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-25"},"text":"Nov. 25, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/2314"},"text":"116 Stat. 2314","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/213/tII/s217/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–213, title II, § 217(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1555"},"text":"126 Stat. 1555","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 101, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282/tI/s103/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 103(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-04"},"text":"Dec. 4, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4195"},"text":"132 Stat. 4195","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id567b5c5c-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id567b5c5d-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 1 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1915-01-28/ch20/s1"},"text":"Jan. 28, 1915, ch. 20, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/38/800"},"text":"38 Stat. 800","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1941-07-11/ch290"},"text":"July 11, 1941, ch. 290","children":[],"tail":", §§ 5, 6(a), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/55/585"},"text":"55 Stat. 585","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Said section has been divided. Provisions relating to operation under the Navy in time of war are placed in sections 3 and 4 of this title, and the remainder is in this section.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This section continues the Coast Guard as a military service and branch of the armed forces of the United States at all times. By the act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1941-07-11"},"text":"July 11, 1941","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/55/585"},"text":"55 Stat. 585","children":[],"tail":" (title 14, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 1), the Coast Guard was constituted a branch of the land and naval forces of the United States at all times. This section therefore merely continues an existing agency and codifies existing law on the military status of the Coast Guard, substituting “armed forces” for “land and naval forces” because of the recent establishment of the Department of the Air Force as an “armed force” rather than as a part of the “land and naval forces”. The Coast Guard is designated a service in the Treasury Department except when operating as a service in the Navy. This is a better definition of the status of the Coast Guard than one which defines it as a service under the Treasury Department in time of peace, because the President is authorized to place the Coast Guard under the Navy in time of emergency, which could be in time of peace."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Changes were made in phraseology. 81st Congress, House Report No. 557.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id567b5c5e-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id567b5c5f-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 101 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s562"},"text":"section 562 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For redesignation of prior sections 1 to 100 not listed below as having been previously repealed or omitted, see Table Showing Redesignations Made by Title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/282"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–282","children":[],"tail":" preceding this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 5, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/497"},"text":"63 Stat. 497","children":[],"tail":", which defined the term “Secretary” for purposes of this title, was omitted in the general amendment of this chapter by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/112/213/tII/s217/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 112–213, title II, § 217(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2012-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2012","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/126/1555"},"text":"126 Stat. 1555","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t14/s105"},"text":"section 105 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 43, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/498"},"text":"63 Stat. 498","children":[],"tail":", provided for relative rank of commissioned officers with respect to Army and Navy officers, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041/s53"},"text":"act Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041, § 53","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/70A/641"},"text":"70A Stat. 641","children":[],"tail":". See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s741"},"text":"section 741 of Title 10","children":[],"tail":", Armed Forces."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 45, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1949-08-04/ch393"},"text":"act Aug. 4, 1949, ch. 393","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/63/498"},"text":"63 Stat. 498","children":[],"tail":", related to permanent grade of Commandant on expiration of term, prior to repeal by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/474/s1/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–474, § 1(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date"